result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Laura Jean Armagost was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Meet with DOC representative within 48 hours.
IID to be installed on any and all vehicles owned or operated by defendant.  Half priced IID approved.
AODA Assessment and follow through on all recommendations of Counselor.

miscConds.notes: Fine and court costs totaling $1,769.00.    If probation/extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant on behalf of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
As a convicted felon, prohibited from possessing a firearm.
Defendant is to undergo any counseling as recommended by Agent.

Not to possess or consume any alcohol or drugs, except for medications as prescribed by a physician and taken only as prescribed.    As a convicted felon, prohibited from voting until civil rights restored.
Maintain absolute sobriety.  Random UA's and drug testing by Agent.

timeConds.notes: Huber release granted, hours and conditions to be set by Sheriff's Dept. where jail sentence will be served.  Day for day credit for successfully completed jail programming to be assigned and monitored by the Criminal Justice Coordinator.  Good time.  Credit for time served of 26 days.  Remanded into the custody of the Bayfield County Sheriff's Dept.

Minutes Filed
Sentencing hearing on June 29, 2016 at 10:00 am.
Letter from Atty. Latzig to Judge Anderson regarding OWI compliance court
Exhibits 1-29 (photographs not scanned)

Defendant Laura Jean Armagost in court with attorney Courtney J Latzig.  Frederick Ian Bourg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Exhibits #1 - #15 marked.  Exhibits #1-#4 rec'd by the Court.  Court gives jurors preliminary instructions.
Jury Trial; Jury Panel sworn.  Selection begins; Judge questions the jurors, D. Milligan absent, A. Montano excused, R. Ratzel-Levoir excused.  DA Bourg questions the jury.  Latzig questions the jury. Court asks the jurors follow-up questions.  Attys take strikes.  Court reviews Pre-empt, those striken were called and excused.  Court thanks jurors not chosen and excused.  Clerk swears in the panel.  Court gives panel initial instructions.  Break taken at 10:58 a.m.  Back on the record at 11:20 a.m. outside presence of jury.  Latzig brings up issue of witnesses with prior convictions.  DA will address with witness.  Jury brought in at 11:30 a.m.  Opening statement of DA Bourg.  Opening statement of Atty Latzig.
Perry Beeksma sworn and qe. by DA Bourg.  Witness identifies the defendant.  Cross by Atty Latzig.  No re-direct; witness is released from subpoena and excused by the Court.
Break taken for lunch at 11:50 a.m.; to be back at 12:55 p.m.  Court directs jurors not to discuss the case with anyone.  
On the record at 12:55 p.m. outside presence of the jury.  Attys indicate they are ready to continue.  Jury brought in.  
Gary Gurske sworn and questioned by DA Bourg.  Left office and traveled down Hwy H toward home.  Noticed a car off the road.  Witness views map of the area and draws a line at the point of the accident.  Exhibit #16 marked.  Witness identifies Exhibit #5; DA moves for admission of Exhibit #5; Court receives with no objections.  Exhibit #17 marked; offered and received with no objection. Witness reviewed Exhibit #12.  Describes the scene of accident and where individual was laying; only one person at the scene.  Vehicle stopped w/ two women, they brought a blanket for the individual.  These two women walked south to look for other individuals.  Exhibit #18 marked, offered and received with no objection.  Exhibit #7 reviewed by the Witness, DA offers this exhibit, court receives with no objection.  Witness shows trees w/o bark.  Photo marked up and marked as Exhibit #19; offered and received by the Court w/no objection.  Was approximately 15 minutes until the EMS arrived at the scene.  Describes green rubber boot outside by individual and another green rubber boot inside of car; did not see deployed airbags; empty alcoholic bottles inside the car.  Cross by Atty Latzig.  Was the first person on the scene; individual did not speak w/witness at the scene; driver side of the car was up against a tree; shows witness Exhibit #18, marks where the green boot was located.  Re-direct by DA Bourg.  No re-cross by Atty Latzig.  Witness excused by the Court, but instructed to stay around.
Scott Eisenhauer sworn and questioned by DA Bourg.  Was Chief of Police for Iron River in Oct. 2014; worked law enforcement 21 years; 12:04 p.m. dispatched to one-car accident on Hwy H; shows map to witness, marks place of accident; Mr. Gurske at the scene; identifies defendant; Ms. Armagost unconcious at the scene; describes visible injuries; inspected vehicle after EMS left the scene; opened driver-side door; driver airbag deployed; bottle of peppermint schnapps in vehicle; boots and clothing in vehicle; no other individuals found at the scene; Witness reviews Exhibits #5 - #15; Exhibit #20 marked, offered and receives w/no objection.  Exhibits #5 - #13 offered by DA Bourg, Court receives w/no objection.  Witness identifies new photo of vehicle and describes photo as zooming in on passenger door; Exhibit #22 marked; Exhibits #21 and #23 marked; offers these exhibits, Court receives w/no objection.  Exhibit #24 marked; witness identifies; exhibit offered and Court receives w/no objection.  Witness circles deployed airbag; zooms in to right of depolyed airbag, Exhibit #25 marked.  Witness explains procedure law enforcement follows w/ unconcious individual to draw blood for evidence.  Exhibit #26 marked; Witness reviews and identifies.  Cross by Atty Latzig; approximately 4 min. from dispatch call until at the scene; photos taken after Ms. Armagost removed from the scene; did not search her person before she was removed; wanted to make sure there was no one under the car, firemen dug dirt from under the car to check under the car.  Witness views Exhibit #12, items found inside the vehicle include 2 cups, 2 beer cans, one boot.  Driver door was closed when got to the scene, was able to open that door when pulled on it; Exhibit #27 marked; offered and received by the Court w/no objection.  Vehicle was impounded; plate and reg. of vehicle came back to Ms. Cameron.  Exhibit #28 marked; Boots were on the driver side of vehicle; offered and received by the Court w/no objection.  Re-direct by DA Bourg; unknown if anyone else had moved the boots; did not enlarge photo (exhibit #28), do not know who did; do not remember the passenger-side airbag was deployed.  Re-cross by Atty Latzig.  Witness excused.  Break taken.
Isaiah Henson sworn and questioned by DA Bourg.  Works as a phlebotomist and explains procedure for drawing blood; reviews exhibit 26.  No cross by Atty Latzig.  Witness is released from subpoena and excused.  DA offers Exhibit #26 and received by the Court w/no objection.
Katherine Smith sworn and questioned by DA Bourg; Employed by State Lab of Hygiene-explains duties; Exhibit #29 marked and reviewed by the Witness; Exhibit #26 reviewed by the Witness; performed secondary examination of the box, tubes and paperwork; describes testing of the blood; 0.242 BAC.  DA moves for admission of exhibit #29 and #16; Court received w/no objection.  No Cross by Atty Latzig.  Witness released from subpoena and excused.
Craig Rudd sworn and questioned by Atty Latzig; Witness reviews Exhibit #28, objection by DA Bourg, jury removed for discussion.  Break taken.  Back on the record.  Atty Latzig requests for hearing on qualifying as an expert witness.  DA Bourg responds.  Court, p-t order indicates time to be given as expert; 907 recited.  DA Bourg requests break to discuss w/ Atty Latzig.  Court allows break.  Atty Latzig  reports no agreement to expert witness.  DA responds.  Atty Latzig, feels she can be successful in Daubert hearing; based on witness' experiences and training; indicates what he would be testifying to.  DA responds.  Court qe. why this should be allowed, did not follow p-t order, did not give State notice.  DA responds.  Atty Latzig questions witness as to qualifications to give expert testimony; training in law enforcement from MN, accident reconstruction, safety for over 10 years.  Witness questioned by DA Bourg.  Break taken for further discussion with Attys.  Back on the record at 4:13 p.m.  Atty Latzig wishes to proceed and defense will stay away from the testimony regarding the seatbelt.  Court makes record re: this issue; Ms. Armagost answers questions of the Court; satisfied no issue of attempting to qualify this witness as an expert; defendant K&V waiving any right post-judgment to claim ineffective of counsel on this issue.  
Jury back in at 4:20 p.m.  DA w/d objection based on stipulation of Attys.  Court informs the jury this witness will testify as a lay witness, and not as an expert.  Questioning of this witness continues by Atty Latzig.  No Cross by DA Bourg.  No further witnesses for Defense.  No rebuttal witnesses for the State.  Jury takes a break for the Attys and Court to conference on instructions.  Court talks w/Defendant about her testifying or not; K&V waive right to testify on her own behalf.  Atty Latzig requests the third element be removed re: priors.  
Court recites inst:  100, 103, 115, 140, 145, 147, 148, 155, 157, 160, 170, 190, 195, 200, 300, 315, 2660C, 2663, Closing Inst, 484, 515, 525, Special Verdict Forms; attys approve all recited.  
Jury brought back in at 5:08 p.m.  Jury Instructions given to the jurors.  Closing Argument by DA Bourg.  Closing Argument by Atty Latzig.  Rebuttal Argument by DA Bourg.  Final instructions given to the Jurors.  Bailiff sworn.  Jury out for deliberation at 5:52 p.m.  
Court discusses w/Attys exhibits to go back to jury; No objections for all photographs to go back; Court directs all exhibits will go back to jury along with instructions.  Atty Latzig requests Exhibit #27 is rec'd by the Court;  Court receives.  DA Bourg not offering Exhibits #14, #15 and #25.  
Court notified at 8:05 p.m. jury has a verdict.  Attys/Parties notified.  Jury brought into the courtroom at 8:13 p.m.  Juror #1044 is foreperson.  Court reviews and reads verdicts:  Count 1 - G; Count 2 - G; Court polls the jurors, all answered affirmative to these verdicts.  Jurors thanked and excused.  
DA asks Court enter judgment on verdicts; Latzig makes no comments; Court accepts jury verdicts; finds G on both counts; enters JOC on Count 2, Count 1 merges into.  Neither Attys are asking for a PSI.  Court vacates bond on this case, remanded to custody of BCSD until sentencing hearing.  

  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 13, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
